  "market_context": "Wednesday session on ETH with previous day high marked as drawn liquidity. London consolidated and took its initial low without strong direction, setting up accumulation ahead of the New York 8:30 news release.",
  "key_observation": "8:30 news created a manipulation move lower below the consolidation range, setting up the AMD framework with anticipated distribution opposite the manipulation, targeting previous day high.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Marked out previous day high on the chart as the drawn liquidity target for the day.",
    "Observed London session consolidating, taking its initial high then its initial low without significant displacement.",
    "Identified the 8:30 news manipulation move lower, framing it as the manipulation leg of an AMD setup.",
    "Anticipated distribution opposite of the manipulation, projecting price higher into previous day high.",
    "Dropped to lower time frame (5M) to seek entry confirmation, looking for a close below the 8:30 opening price and the series of down-close candles.",
    "Confirmed the close below the series of down-close candles indicating change in state of delivery.",
    "Applied a box setup waiting for a retest of the manipulation low before expansion higher for proper risk-to-reward.",
    "Entered on the retest with stop below the manipulation low and target at previous day high."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price reached and hit previous day high, completing the AMD distribution leg as anticipated.",
  "lessons": "When 8:30 news manipulates against the daily bias, treat it as the manipulation phase of AMD and anticipate distribution into the drawn liquidity (PDH/PDL). Use box setup with retest entry for optimal risk-to-reward.",
